  "description": {
    "rendered": "<p class=\"attachment\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/The-Power-of-Kawaii.jpg?ssl=1\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/The-Power-of-Kawaii.jpg?fit=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"attachment-medium size-medium\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/The-Power-of-Kawaii.jpg?w=467&amp;ssl=1 467w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/The-Power-of-Kawaii.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/The-Power-of-Kawaii.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/The-Power-of-Kawaii.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/The-Power-of-Kawaii.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Twin polar bear cubs (Ursus maritimus), about 3 months old, inside a snow den. (Their mother was nearby, tranquilized, and having her condition assessed by Canadian Wildlife Service polar bear biologists.) The polar bear is listed as a Vulnerable species on the IUCN Red List (designated in 2005), and as a Threatened species under the U.S. Endangered Species Act (listed in 2008). Polar bear maternity denning area, Wapusk National Park, Manitoba, Canada.</p>\n"
  },
  "caption": {
    "rendered": "<p>Via Zoo Atlanta: Polar Bear Cubs (Endangered)</p>\n"
  },
